# Core Prototyping Rules

## Component Library
- Always use shadcn/ui primitives from `src/components/ui/`
- Never write raw `<button>`, `<input>`, `<select>` — use the shadcn equivalents
- If a needed component isn't installed, add it: `npx shadcn@latest add <name>`
- Shared prototype chrome goes in `src/components/prototype/` (nav, frames, shells)

## Styling
- Use Tailwind utility classes exclusively — no `style={{}}` inline styles
- Never write custom CSS unless updating CSS variables in `globals.css`
- Colors, font sizes, and spacing must use Tailwind scale values
- Respect the CSS variable tokens from shadcn (`--primary`, `--background`, etc.)
- After applying branding, always update the CSS variables in `globals.css`

## File & Route Structure
- Every new screen lives at `src/app/(screens)/[screen-name]/page.tsx`
- After creating any new screen, register it in `src/app/page.tsx` prototype index
- Co-locate screen-specific components next to their `page.tsx` (not in global components)
- Only truly shared components go in `src/components/prototype/`

## TypeScript
- Every component must have typed props — use `interface` for prop definitions
- Use `type` for union types and utility types
- Export types that are used across files from `src/lib/types.ts`
- Never use `any` — use `unknown` + type guards if the shape is uncertain

## State Management
- Use React `useState` and `useContext` only — no Zustand, Redux, or similar
- For shared state across screens, use React Context with a provider in `layout.tsx`
- Keep state as local as possible (closest component that needs it)

## Code Readability (designers read this code)
- Keep components under 150 lines — extract sub-components freely
- Use descriptive variable names, not abbreviations
- Add a one-line comment above any non-obvious logic
- Group JSX with blank lines between logical sections

## Images and Assets
- Use `/public/` for static assets used in prototypes
- For placeholder images, use `https://picsum.photos/{width}/{height}` or `https://api.dicebear.com/` for avatars
- Brand logos go in `branding/logos/` and should be copied to `public/` when used

## Prototype Index
- `src/app/page.tsx` is the visual dashboard — always keep it updated
- Each screen entry must include: name, description, route, and which device frame it uses
